quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  64,1,"Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is on the earth glorifies God. His is the Sovereignty and His is the praise, and He is Powerful over all things"
  64,2,He it is Who created you; among you are disbelievers and among you are believers. And God sees whatsoever you do
  64,3,"He created the heavens and the earth in truth and formed you, then made beautiful your forms, and unto Him is the journey’s end"
  64,4,"He knows whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth, and He knows what you hide and what you disclose; God knows what lies within breasts"
  64,5,"Has not the account come to you of those who disbelieved aforetime such that they tasted the evil consequences of their affair, and theirs shall be a painful punishment"
  64,6,"That is because their messengers brought them clear proofs, at which they said, “Shall a human being guide us?” So they disbelieved and turned away; yet God is beyond need. And God is Self-Sufficient, Praised"
  64,7,"Those who disbelieve claim that they will not be resurrected. Say, “Yea! By my Lord! Surely you shall be resurrected. Then you shall be informed of that which you did; and that is easy for God.”"
  64,8,So believe in God and His Messenger and the light We have sent down. God is Aware of whatsoever you do
  64,9,"The day that He gathers you for the Day of Gathering, that is the Day of Mutual Dispossession. And whosoever believes in God and works righteousness, He will absolve him of his evil deeds and cause him to enter Gardens with rivers running below, to abide therein forever. That is the great triumph"
  64,10,"And those who disbelieve and deny Our signs, they are the inhabitants of the Fire, abiding therein. What an evil journey’s end"
  64,11,"No misfortune befalls, save by God’s Leave. And whosoever believes in God, He guides his heart. And God is Knower of all things"
  64,12,Obey God and obey the Messenger. Then if you turn away—only the clear proclamation is incumbent upon Our Messenger
  64,13,"God, there is no god but He, and in God let the believers trust"
  64,14,"O you who believe! Among your spouses and your children there is indeed an enemy unto you; so be wary of them. Yet if you pardon, forbear, and forgive, then truly God is Forgiving, Merciful"
  64,15,Your property and your children are only a trial; and God—with Him is a great reward
  64,16,"So reverence God as much as you are able. Listen, obey, and spend; that is better for your souls. And whosoever is shielded from the avarice of his soul, it is they who shall prosper"
  64,17,"If you lend unto God a goodly loan, He will multiply it for you and forgive you; and God is Thankful, Clement"
  64,18,"Knower of the Unseen and the seen, the Mighty, the Wise"